The regex checks if the entire string from start (`^`) to end (`$`) matches the characters enclosed in the `[]`, which is a range of from capital A through capital Z (`A-Z`, the special &quot;space&quot; character `\s`, and other non-word characters `\W`, matching one or more times. You could fine-tune this to make sure that it matches at least one capital letter, followed optionally by spaces, commas, exclamation points, etc. It all depends on your use cases and what the expected input vs. output would be

